
fyi:man pages seem to not exist on a steam deck but --help is present
fyi:vim is installed
fyi: steamdeck is running what appears to be a stripped down debian

Step 1 enable ssh server so you can use a real keyboard 
https://shendrick.net/Gaming/2022/05/30/sshonsteamdeck.html

Step 2 get ip address
ip addr
https://opensource.com/article/18/5/how-find-ip-address-linux


Step 3 get current username to use to login for putty
step 4. install putty or some other decent ssh client
step 5. add port rules for java minecraft using iptables






save iptables and make them persistant so when the device restarts you dont have to do this again

https://askubuntu.com/questions/66890/how-can-i-make-a-specific-set-of-iptables-rules-permanent





bonus:history dump

